<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="387" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,356,743]" box="[151,888,356,383]" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,356,382]" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">Description.</emphasis>
Pale green, usually with black frontal spot (
<figureCitation box="[791,875,356,383]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–28" captionStartId="10.[151,264,2000,2024]" captionTargetBox="[162,1424,185,1973]" captionTargetId="figure-25@10.[158,1430,181,1976]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 5–28. Macropsis spp., lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4404165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4404165/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,356,743]" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">
Abdominal apodemes of 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[501,517,392,406]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">nd</superScript>
tergite in male with small round notches on inner edges; sternal apodemes with wide bases and narrow angulate tips (
<figureCitation box="[569,705,428,455]" captionStart="FIGURES 92–111" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1892,1916]" captionTargetBox="[184,1406,191,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-16@17.[174,1414,181,1868]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 92–111. Macropsis notata (92–96), M. ocellata (97–101), M. gravesteini (102–106), and M. prasina (107–111) from European Russia (92–93, 97–98, 102–103, 107–109) and Southeastern Kazakhstan (94–96, 99–101, 104–106, 110–111). 92, 94, 97, 99, 102, 104, 107, 110―male 2nd abdominal apodemes; 93, 95, 98, 100, 103, 105, 108, 111―penis, lateral view; 96, 101, 106, 109―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4404171" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4404171/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">Figs. 97, 99</figureCitation>
). Penis in side view rather narrow, without extension in middle of stem (
<figureCitation box="[219,371,464,491]" captionStart="FIGURES 92–111" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1892,1916]" captionTargetBox="[184,1406,191,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-16@17.[174,1414,181,1868]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 92–111. Macropsis notata (92–96), M. ocellata (97–101), M. gravesteini (102–106), and M. prasina (107–111) from European Russia (92–93, 97–98, 102–103, 107–109) and Southeastern Kazakhstan (94–96, 99–101, 104–106, 110–111). 92, 94, 97, 99, 102, 104, 107, 110―male 2nd abdominal apodemes; 93, 95, 98, 100, 103, 105, 108, 111―penis, lateral view; 96, 101, 106, 109―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4404171" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4404171/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">Figs. 98, 100</figureCitation>
). 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[404,420,464,478]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">nd</superScript>
valvulae of ovipositor with 3–5 preapical teeth (
<figureCitation box="[965,1063,464,491]" captionStart="FIGURES 92–111" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1892,1916]" captionTargetBox="[184,1406,191,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-16@17.[174,1414,181,1868]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 92–111. Macropsis notata (92–96), M. ocellata (97–101), M. gravesteini (102–106), and M. prasina (107–111) from European Russia (92–93, 97–98, 102–103, 107–109) and Southeastern Kazakhstan (94–96, 99–101, 104–106, 110–111). 92, 94, 97, 99, 102, 104, 107, 110―male 2nd abdominal apodemes; 93, 95, 98, 100, 103, 105, 108, 111―penis, lateral view; 96, 101, 106, 109―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4404171" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4404171/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">Fig. 101</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,356,743]" box="[199,942,500,527]" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">
Body length (including tegmina): 
<specimenCount box="[580,603,501,527]" pageId="6" pageNumber="387" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
, 
<quantity box="[615,753,501,527]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.1" metricValueMax="4.3" metricValueMin="3.9" pageId="6" pageNumber="387" unit="mm" value="4.1" valueMax="4.3" valueMin="3.9">3.9–4.3 mm</quantity>
; 
<specimenCount box="[765,786,501,527]" pageId="6" pageNumber="387" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
, 
<quantity box="[800,938,500,527]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.7" metricValueMax="4.9" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="387" unit="mm" value="4.7" valueMax="4.9" valueMin="4.5">4.5–4.9 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,356,743]" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">
Specimens from European 
<collectingCountry box="[505,580,536,562]" name="Russia" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">Russia</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[596,731,536,563]" captionStart="FIGURES 92–111" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1892,1916]" captionTargetBox="[184,1406,191,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-16@17.[174,1414,181,1868]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 92–111. Macropsis notata (92–96), M. ocellata (97–101), M. gravesteini (102–106), and M. prasina (107–111) from European Russia (92–93, 97–98, 102–103, 107–109) and Southeastern Kazakhstan (94–96, 99–101, 104–106, 110–111). 92, 94, 97, 99, 102, 104, 107, 110―male 2nd abdominal apodemes; 93, 95, 98, 100, 103, 105, 108, 111―penis, lateral view; 96, 101, 106, 109―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4404171" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4404171/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">Figs. 97–98</figureCitation>
) and Southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[947,1078,536,562]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[1094,1243,536,563]" captionStart="FIGURES 92–111" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1892,1916]" captionTargetBox="[184,1406,191,1858]" captionTargetId="figure-16@17.[174,1414,181,1868]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 92–111. Macropsis notata (92–96), M. ocellata (97–101), M. gravesteini (102–106), and M. prasina (107–111) from European Russia (92–93, 97–98, 102–103, 107–109) and Southeastern Kazakhstan (94–96, 99–101, 104–106, 110–111). 92, 94, 97, 99, 102, 104, 107, 110―male 2nd abdominal apodemes; 93, 95, 98, 100, 103, 105, 108, 111―penis, lateral view; 96, 101, 106, 109―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4404171" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4404171/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">Figs. 99–101</figureCitation>
) have no significant differences in shape of apodemes and genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
