<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="387" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,356,743]" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,644,670]" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">Distribution.</emphasis>
Central and Southern Europe, Southern Urals, 
<collectingCountry box="[875,1009,644,670]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
. In Central Asia was found only in one locality on Ferghana Mtn. Range, despite the fact that 
<taxonomicName box="[753,831,680,707]" class="Ascidiacea" family="Polycitoridae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Enterogona" pageId="6" pageNumber="387" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alba">
<emphasis box="[753,831,680,707]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="387">S. alba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widespread in these parts in natural and agricultural landscapes. Introduced to North America (
<bibRefCitation author="Hamilton, K. G. A." box="[625,807,716,743]" pageId="6" pageNumber="387" pagination="875 - 932" refId="ref14095" refString="Hamilton, K. G. A. (1980) Contribution to the study of the world Macropsini (Rhynchota: Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Canadian Entomologist, 112 (9), 875 - 932. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / Ent 112875 - 9" type="journal article" year="1980">Hamilton, 1980</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
